Statistical Modelling III
MPG - model selection

Week 11

Data

mpg

Cleaning

mpg <- 
  mpg %>% 
  select(-hwy)
mpg %>% 
  count(manufacturer)
mpg <- 
  mpg %>% 
  mutate(
    manufacturer = fct_lump_min(manufacturer, min = 10)
  ) 
mpg %>% 
  count(manufacturer)
mpg %>% count(model)
mpg <- 
  mpg %>% 
  select(-model)
mpg
mpg %>% count(trans)
mpg <- 
  mpg %>% 
  mutate(
    trans = ifelse(
      str_detect(trans, "auto"), 
      "auto", 
      "manual"
    )
  )
mpg %>% count(trans)
mpg %>% count(drv)
mpg %>% count(fl)
mpg <- 
  mpg %>% 
  mutate(
    fl = fct_lump_min(fl, 10)
  )
mpg %>% count(fl)
mpg %>% count(class)
mpg
mpg <- 
  mpg %>% 
  mutate(
    across(where(is.character), factor)
  )
mpg

So we have two models:

Model 1: cty ~ manufacturer + displ + year + cyl + trans + drv + fl + class
Model 2: cty ~ manufacturer + displ + year + cyl + trans + drv + class

We will decide between them using 5-fold CV with RSME.

CV

Split data

nrow(mpg) / 5
## [1] 46.8
folds <- rep(1:5, each = 47)
folds <- folds[1:nrow(mpg)]
mpg_CV <-
  mpg %>%
  add_column(
    fold = sample(folds)
    )
mpg_CV

Check balance

mpg_CV %>% count(fold)

Fit models and get RMSE

RMSE_M1 <- double(5)
RMSE_M2 <- double(5)
for(i in 1:5){
  # Get test and train
  train <- mpg_CV %>% filter(fold != i)
  test <- mpg_CV %>% filter(fold == i)
  # Fit model to train
  M1 <- lm(
    cty ~ manufacturer + displ + year + cyl + trans + drv + fl + class,
    data = train)
  M2 <- lm(
    cty ~ manufacturer + displ + year + cyl + trans + drv + class, 
    data = train)
  # Predict for test
  M1_pred <- predict(M1, newdata = test)
  M2_pred <- predict(M2, newdata = test)
  # Calculate RMSE
  RMSE_M1[i] <- sqrt(mean((test$cty - M1_pred)^2))
  RMSE_M2[i] <- sqrt(mean((test$cty - M2_pred)^2))
}
mean(RMSE_M1)
## [1] 2.152645
mean(RMSE_M2)
## [1] 2.011096

So M1 has lower CV RMSE, so I will use this.

So final model is

Model 1: cty ~ manufacturer + displ + year + cyl + trans + drv + fl + class

Final model

final_model <- lm(
    cty ~ manufacturer + displ + year + cyl + trans + drv + fl + class,
    data = mpg)
gglm::gglm(final_model)
